C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5489c8a86bb3f7980ce8670d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20nurses%20are%20turning%20to%20gig%20work%20apps%20to%20find%20shifts%20at%20hospitals%20and%20other%20medical%20facilities.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%20%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGig%20work%20has%20expanded%20to%20include%20nurses%20at%20hospitals%20and%20medical%20facilities%2C%20per%20a%20new%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20nurses%20who%20work%20this%20way%20face%20challenges%20similar%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fuber%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%3C%2Fa%3E%20drivers%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENursing%20represents%20a%20high-stakes%20use%20case%20of%20gig%20work%20apps%2C%20one%20of%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-grubhub-uber-workers-gig-work-feels-like-a-job-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGig%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20expanded%20to%20the%20nurses%20who%20care%20for%20patients%20in%20hospitals%20and%20care%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20coming%20with%20some%20of%20the%20same%20challenges%20that%20delivery%20and%20rideshare%20contractors%20have%20already%20pointed%20to%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApps%20like%20CareRev%2C%20Clipboard%20Health%2C%20and%20ShiftKey%20have%20taken%20an%20approach%20similar%20to%20the%20one%20companies%20like%20Uber%20and%20Instacart%20have%20used%20to%20build%20up%20their%20workforces%2C%20and%20applied%20it%20to%20nursing%20at%20hospitals%2C%20care%20homes%2C%20and%20other%20medical%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20report%2C%20which%20the%20Roosevelt%20Institute%20released%20a%20summary%20of%20this%20week%2C%20found%20that%20medical%20facilities%20often%20turn%20to%20gig%20nursing%20services%20as%20a%20way%20to%20cut%20expenses%2C%20especially%20under%20the%20tutelage%20of%20private%20equity%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedical%20professionals%20on%20the%20apps%2C%20which%20the%20report%20collectively%20calls%20%26quot%3BUber%20for%20Nursing%2C%26quot%3B%20also%20face%20many%20of%20the%20same%20issues%20that%20other%20gig%20workers%20do%2C%20from%20low%20pay%20to%20having%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-walmart-spark-gig-workers-share-weirdest-deactivation-stories-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccounts%20on%20the%20platforms%20deactivated%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20little%20or%20no%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20apps%20make%20pitches%20that%20are%20attractive%20to%20the%20nurses%20themselves%2C%20Katie%20Wells%2C%20a%20senior%20Fellow%20at%20think%20tank%20Groundwork%20Collaborative%20and%20one%20of%20the%20report's%20authors%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%20Wells%20wrote%20the%20report%20with%20Funda%20Ustek%20Spilda%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20at%20King's%20College%20London%20and%20a%20research%20associate%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oxford's%20Oxford%20Internet%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFull-time%20nursing%20jobs%20often%20involve%20putting%20in%20long%20hours%20as%20well%20as%20working%20night%20or%20weekend%20shifts.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fim-a-covid-nurse-im-burned-out-tempted-to-quit-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECOVID's%20strain%20on%20hospitals%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20medical%20facilities%20also%20pushed%20many%20nurses%20to%20quit%20or%20consider%20finding%20other%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20rideshare%20and%20delivery%20companies%2C%20the%20apps%20say%20that%20they%20offer%20nurses%20more%20choices%20over%20how%20and%20when%20they%20work.%20ShiftKey's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shiftkey.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20says%20that%20its%20users%20have%20%26quot%3Bthe%20freedom%20to%20make%20choices%20best%20suited%20to%20their%20lives%26quot%3B%20including%20how%20much%20they%20earn%20and%20%26quot%3Btheir%20relationship%20with%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20burned-out%20nurse%2C%20that%20can%20be%20an%20appealing%20pitch%2C%20Wells%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20almost%20no%20flexibility%20and%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20is%20no%20wonder%20that%20these%20apps%20become%20attractive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWells%20and%20Spilda%20interviewed%2029%20nurses%20and%20nursing%20assistants%20for%20their%20study.%20The%20interviewees%20all%20used%20at%20least%20one%20gig%20work%20app%20to%20find%20nursing%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20delivery%20and%20rideshare%20contractors%2C%20nurses%20who%20use%20the%20apps%20must%20claim%20jobs%20through%20them.%20The%20nursing%20apps%20often%20charge%20a%20fee%20for%20access%2C%20and%20workers%20bid%20with%20their%20pay%20rates.%20The%20user%20who%20offers%20the%20lowest%20pay%20gets%20the%20shift%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20the%20shift%2C%20however%2C%20can%20be%20tricky.%20When%20they%20show%20up%20for%20a%20gig%2C%20the%20nurses%20often%20have%20to%20navigate%20the%20facility%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20have%20never%20worked%20there%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20most%20hospitals%20and%20medical%20facilities%2C%20no%20orientations%20are%20required%20for%20gig%20nurses%20and%20nursing%20assistants%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20reads.%20%26quot%3BWorkers%20do%20not%20know%20where%20supply%20closets%20are%20located%2C%20how%20to%20access%20patient%20portals%20with%20medical%20histories%20and%20current%20medication%20lists%2C%20and%20whom%20to%20contact%20in%20the%20chain%20of%20command.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20like%20Uber%20drivers%20or%20Instacart%20delivery%20workers%2C%20nurses%20who%20use%20the%20apps%20don't%20have%20a%20boss%20to%20contact%20when%20things%20go%20wrong.%20One%20Oregon-based%20nurse%20interviewed%20for%20the%20study%20said%20that%20she%20was%20barred%20from%20Clipboard%20Health's%20app%20for%20two%20weeks%20after%20she%20had%20a%20hernia%20on%20the%20job%20and%20had%20to%20leave%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20instance%2C%20the%20same%20nurse%20said%20that%20she%20went%20to%20work%20with%20COVID%20after%20learning%20that%20she%20couldn't%20cancel%20her%20shift%20without%20losing%20%26quot%3Battendance%20points%26quot%3B%20and%20hurting%20her%20chances%20of%20getting%20gigs%20in%20the%20future%2C%20the%20report%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20sucks%20that%20there's%20nobody%20that%20you%20can%20get%20ahold%20of%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20nurse%20told%20Wells%20and%20Spilda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20as%20if%20AI%20has%20eaten%20the%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20apps%20also%20advertise%20that%20nurses%20can%20make%20more%20on%20their%20platforms%20than%20at%20other%20jobs.%20One%20nurse%20interviewed%20by%20the%20researchers%20said%20she%20made%20gross%20pay%20of%20%2423%20an%20hour%20on%20ShiftKey.%20That%20dropped%20to%20around%20%2413%20an%20hour%20after%20accounting%20for%20fees%20that%20she%20paid%20to%20ShiftKey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20challenges%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%2019%20of%20the%2029%20people%20interviewed%20planned%20to%20continue%20working%20for%20the%20apps%2C%20though%20some%20also%20said%20they%20also%20had%20jobs%20in%20other%20industries%20to%20make%20enough%20money%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20gig%20nursing%20apps%20are%20often%20used%20by%20facilities%20that%20are%20trying%20to%20save%20money%20and%20are%20under%20pressure%20to%20produce%20returns%20for%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWells%20told%20BI%20that%20bringing%20the%20gig%20economy%20to%20medical%20care%20creates%20risks%20not%20present%20in%20food%20delivery%20or%20rideshare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stakes%20are%20higher%20because%20this%20has%20to%20do%20with%20patient%20safety%2C%20and%20the%20immediacy%20of%20health%20and%20care%20makes%20things%20more%20palpable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShiftMed%2C%20which%20employs%20its%20nurses%20as%20W2%20employees%20but%20still%20offers%20them%20much%20of%20the%20flexibility%20of%20gig%20work%2C%20said%20that%20it%20deactivates%20nurses'%20accounts%20for%20various%20reasons%2C%20from%20patient%20safety%20to%20legal%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNurses%20file%20an%20appeal%20by%20submitting%20a%20formal%20review%20through%20the%20app%20or%20support%20channel%2C%20after%20which%20ShiftMed%20conducts%20an%20internal%20investigation%2C%20reviews%20records%2C%20and%20determines%20the%20next%20steps%2C%26quot%3B%20CEO%20Todd%20Walrath%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20that%20it%20also%20offers%20an%20orientation%20so%20that%20users%20%26quot%3Bare%20fully%20prepared%20for%20any%20clinical%20setting%20by%20aligning%20health%20system-specific%20requirements%2C%20such%20as%20training%20or%20shadowing%20before%20they%20begin%20shifts%2C%26quot%3B%20Walrath%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECareRev%2C%20Clipboard%20Health%2C%20and%20ShiftKey%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20nurse%20who%20works%20as%20an%20independent%20contractor%20with%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-for-nursing-apps-show-issues-across-expanding-gig-economy-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734776222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6765963d6c531c315b898d60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22h