e.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20daughter%2C%20Carter%2C%20started%20struggling%20with%20reading%2C%20we%20thought%20it%20was%20related%20to%20her%20late%20birthday%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20almost%20everybody%20else%20in%20her%20class%20was%20a%20whole%20year%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20father%2C%20Paul%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20that%20she%20should%20repeat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdropping-son-off-kindergarten-tough-realization-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekindergarten%20in%20her%20public%20school%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20her%20first%20year%2C%20she'd%20been%20put%20in%20a%20Response%20to%20Intervention%20(RTI)%20program%20to%20improve%20her%20literacy%20skills.%20However%2C%20at%20the%20parent%2Fteacher%20conference%20during%20her%20second%20year%2C%20we%20were%20told%20she%20wouldn't%20receive%20RTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20make%20sense%20because%20she%20wasn't%20progressing.%20Her%20self-confidence%20was%20low%20because%20it%20seemed%20like%20everyone%20else%20around%20her%20could%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20heard%20from%20the%20teacher%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20OK.%20We're%20gonna%20let%20your%20kid%20slide%20through.%26quot%3B%20Being%20a%20child%20myself%20who%20was%20allowed%20to%20slide%2C%20I%20hit%20the%20brakes.%20At%20that%20moment%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20kid's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20the%20kid%20that's%20just%20going%20to%20slide%20through.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b775783d-e870-436d-ac05-40f5b7531a0f%5C%22%3EWe%20had%20to%20employ%20a%20reading%20tutor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20issue%20was%20the%20school%20district%20didn't%20teach%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Feducational-kids-apps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephonics%20for%20reading%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%2C%20the%20kids%20are%20taught%20to%20scan%20the%20page%20for%20picture%20clue