Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERyan%20Crawley%2C%20a%20former%20elementary%20school%20teacher%20who%20left%20his%20job%20to%20become%20a%20freelance%20writer.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ryan%20Crawley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%2010%20years%20in%20elementary%20education%2C%20I%20decided%20I%20no%20longer%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20teacher.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20wanted%20a%20more%20flexible%20job%20that%20allowed%20me%20to%20stay%20at%20home%20with%20my%20kids.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20time%20allows%2C%20I'm%20able%20to%20make%20more%20money%20than%20I%20did%20as%20a%20teacher%20and%20have%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20went%20into%20education%2C%20I%20did%20so%20with%20the%20best%20intentions.%20Being%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-corporate-job-to-become-an-elementary-school-teacher-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emale%20elementary%20school%20teacher%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20sort%20of%20like%20being%20a%20unicorn.%20It%20is%20extremely%20rare%20for%20a%20man%20to%20be%20teaching%20early%20elementary.%20There%20were%20plenty%20of%20single-mom%20families%20in%20the%20area%20where%20I%20lived%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20many%20students%20didn't%20have%20a%20male%20role%20model%20at%20home%20to%20inspire%20them%2C%20so%20I%20thought%20I%20could%20fill%20this%20void.%20I%20took%20the%20responsibility%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20ten%20years%20in%20the%20field%2C%20I%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-teaching-job-after-decades-now-work-at-costco-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etap%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20few%20reasons.%20None%20of%20the%20reasons%20really%20had%20to%20do%20with%20the%20students%20themselves.%20The%20pay%20wasn't%20great%20(after%2010%20years%20of%20teaching%20I%20was%20still%20taking%20home%20just%20around%20%243%2C000%20a%20month)%20and%20I%20didn't%20enjoy%20the%20politics%20of%20teaching.%20But%2C%20the%20most%20important%20reason%20was%20probably%20that%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20ready%20to%20start%20a%20family.%20She%20often%20works%20long%20hours%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20someone%20else%20to%20raise%20my%20children.%20I%20thought%20I%20could%20find%20a%20way%20to%20contribute%20financially%20and%20still%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstay-at-home-dad-career-lessons-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20with%20the%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d93937e-7bd2-4ac2-ba26-a30dd695bc44%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBecoming%20a%20freelance%20writer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20went%20into%20education%2C%20I%20had%20been%20a%20journalist%20for%20a%20few%20years.%20It%20wasn't%20something%20I%20really%20enjoyed%20at%20the%20time%20and%20I%20didn't%20see%20myself%20wanting%20to%20cover%20mundane%20board%20meetings%20forever.%20If%20you%20ever%20suffer%20from%20insomnia%2C%20just%20drop%20in%20on%20these%20meetings%20occasionally.%20It's%20like%20an%20instant%20sleeping%20pill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20a%20decent%20writer.%20I've%20certainly%20read%20worse%20over%20the%20years%20from%20people%20who%20made%20their%20living%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreelance-writer-failed-went-back-full-time-job-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessional%20writers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20while%20I%20was%20still%20teaching%2C%20I%20joined%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-started-upwork-clients-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUpwork%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20website%20that%20connects%20freelancers%20with%20those%20looking%20to%20hire%20contract%20workers.%20Upwork%20allows%20people%20or%20companies%20to%20search%20for%20a%20specific%20type%20of%20writer%20they%20are%20looking%20for%20to%20complete%20their%20project%20at%20hand.%20You%20are%20competing%20against%20other%20writers%20who%20are%20also%20applying%2C%20but%20Upwork%20is%20a%20great%20tool%20to%20use%20when%20you%20are%20first%20attempting%20a%20freelance%20career.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETo%20begin%2C%20I%20set%20my%20fees%20low%20to%20get%20my%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%20Then%20it%20wasn't%20long%20before%20I%20had%20clients%20who%20were%20asking%20me%20to%20write%20for%20them%20on%20either%20a%20weekly%20or%20monthly%20basis.%20As%20an%20unexpected%20bonus%2C%20most%20of%20the%20topics%20I%20covered%20genuinely%20interested%20me.%20Health%20and%20fitness%2C%20education%2C%20and%20even%20ghostwriting%20children's%20books%20were%20all%20things%20I%20enjoyed%20writing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20was%20getting%20paid%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e89097dd-5e02-4b81-a035-6a165c504790%5C%22%3EFast%20forward%20four%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20was%20wrapping%20up%20my%20last%20weeks%20in%20the%20classroom%20before%20the%20school%20year%20ended%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20could%20go%20give%20my%20notice%20that%20I%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-teaching-go-back-school-launch-satellites-unfulfilling-switch-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20be%20coming%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20teach%20the%20following%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20just%20made%20%246%2C000%20in%20one%20month%20from%20freelancing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20was%20while%20I%20was%20still%20teaching.%20I%20would%20definitely%20miss%20my%20students%20and%20all%20the%20friends%20I%20had%20made%2C%20but%20being%20able%20to%20set%20my%20own%20schedule%2C%20work%20from%20home%2C%20and%20raise%20my%20kids%20was%20something%20I%20could%20not%20pass%20up.%20My%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20having%20children%20later%20on%20in%20life%2C%20and%20the%20math%20showed%20me%20I%20would%20probably%20not%20get%20the%20chance%20to%20spend%20as%20much%20time%20with%20my%20kids%20as%20other%20fathers%2C%20so%20I%20switched%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226af0237e-867d-4033-b63f-25beb46529f5%5C%22%3EMy%20plan%20is%20mostly%20working%20well%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20admit%2C%20I%20underestimated%20how%20much%20time%20I%20would%20have%20to%20write%20while%20taking%20care%20of%20two%20babies%20at%20home.%20I've%20really%20had%20to%20narrow%20down%20my%20client%20list%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20picking%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20truly%20worthwhile.%20Now%20I%20only%20accept%20writing%20assignments%20I%20can%20get%20excited%20about.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThough%20I%20only%20have%20about%2015%20hours%20of%20free%20time%20at%20home%20a%20week%20where%20I%20can%20focus%20on%20writing%2C%20I%20have%20made%20the%20most%20of%20it.%20In%20fact%2C%20you%20can%20find%20my%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftricks-get-kids-interested-reading-books-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren's%20books%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BEllie%20and%20Jack%3A%20Third%20Grade%20Ghost%20Hunters%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BEllie%20and%20Jack%3A%20Third%20Grade%20Vampire%20Hunters%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20Amazon%20and%20other%20sites.%20I%20always%20wanted%20to%20write%20children's%20books%2C%20and%20after%20helping%20thousands%20of%20children%20become%20better%20readers%20over%20the%20years%2C%20I%20think%20I%20have%20a%20pretty%20good%20idea%20on%20the%20types%20of%20stories%20they%20love%20to%20read.%20Weaving%20my%20teaching%20past%20into%20my%20current%20career%20has%20been%20a%20joy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20one%20child%20getting%20ready%20for%20kindergarten%20and%20the%20other%20just%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20away%2C%20it%20won't%20be%20long%20before%20I%20will%20have%20more%20time%20to%20write%20once%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-teaching-job-to-be-freelance-writer-doubled-income-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2