%20to%20officials%2C%20coupled%20with%20%26quot%3Bthe%20long%20and%20troubling%20history%20of%20unspeakable%20maltreatment%20against%20incarcerated%20people%20by%20the%20very%20actors%20charged%20with%20their%20protection%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%2C%20has%20created%20a%20landscape%20where%20%26quot%3Bthe%20power%20that%20prison%20officials%20have%20over%20incarcerated%20persons%20is%20sure%20to%20be%20abused.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20BI's%20sample%2C%20a%20few%20attorneys%20successfully%20proved%20mindset%2C%20sometimes%20by%20obtaining%20explicit%20circumstantial%20evidence%2C%20such%20as%20email%20exchanges%20introduced%20in%20the%20case%20of%20one%20Illinois%20prisoner%20that%20show%20prison%20healthcare%20providers%20floated%20the%20possibility%20of%20sending%20him%20to%20hospice%20care%20after%20his%20oncologist%20recommended%20treatment%20that%20would%20cost%20%2415%2C000%20a%20month.%20But%20such%20cases%20were%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227793%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Washington%20D.C.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67535fc78fbb2783ed306554%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225198%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%201994%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20Farmer%20v.%20Brennan%2C%20ruled%20that%20prison%20officials%20were%20liable%20for%20Eighth%20Amendment%20violations%20only%20if%20they%20acted%20with%20%26quot%3Bdeliberate%20indifference%26quot%3B%20to%20a%20prisoner's%20suffering.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20sitting%20judges%20would%20comment%20to%20BI%20about%20the%20deliberate-indifference%20standard%3B%20some%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20interview%20requests%2C%20while%20others%20declined%20to%20comment.%20One%20who%20did%2C%20Lawrence%20Piersol%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20South%20Dakota%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263149-jason-dunkelberger-v-john-story-complaint%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecided%20a%20case%20under%20the%20standard%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20in%202020%20by%20a%20prisoner%20named%20Jason%20Dunkelberger.%20While%20incarcerated%20at%20the%20South%20Dakota%20State%20Penitentiary%2C%20Dunkelberger%20said%2C%20the%20tips%20of%20his%20fingers%20were%20severed%20by%20a%20metal%20shear%20in%20the%20prison%20machine%20shop%20that%20he'd%20never%20been%20trained%20to%20use%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263160-jason-dunkelberger-v-john-story-deposition%23document%2Fp3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20deposition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20said%20he%20was%20told%20he'd%20be%20sent%20to%20solitary%20if%20he%20refused%20the%20assignment%2C%20given%20to%20him%20by%20a%20fellow%20prisoner%20put%20in%20charge%20by%20the%20machine%20shop's%20supervisor.%20He%20said%20he%20waited%2090%20minutes%20before%20being%20sent%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20where%20the%20fingers%20were%20amputated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20South%20Dakota%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20lawsuit%2C%20Dunkelberger%20argued%20that%20prison%20staff%20had%20violated%20his%20constitutional%20rights%20by%20failing%20to%20keep%20him%20safe.%20Because%20the%20directive%20to%20use%20the%20machine%20had%20come%20from%20a%20prisoner%2C%20and%20not%20an%20officer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263162-jason-dunkelberger-v-john-story-decision%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPiersol%20ruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20officials%20couldn't%20be%20considered%20deliberately%20indifferent.%20Piersol%20said%20his%20decision%20spoke%20for%20itself%2C%20but%20he%20agreed%20to%20comment%20on%20Eighth%20Amendment%20cases%20generally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20difficult%20for%20a%20prisoner%20to%20succeed%2C%26quot%3B%20Piersol%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20sometimes%20there%20are%20some%20decent%20settlements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDunkelberger's%20claim%20couldn't%20meet%20that%20high%20bar.%20Vandevender's%20didn't%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDonovan%20Frank%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20with%20the%20District%20of%20Minnesota%2C%20granted%20the%20prison%20officials%20qualified%20immunity%20in%20the%20Vandevender%20case%2C%20finding%20that%20he%20had%20failed%20to%20prove%20they%20%26quot%3Bwere%20subjectively%20aware%20of%20a%20substantial%20risk%20posed%20by%20the%20wooden%20boards.%26quot%3B%20Even%20if%20they%20should%20have%20known%20that%20leaving%20them%20unsecured%20violated%20Rush%20City's%20tool%20policy%2C%20Frank%20wrote%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20satisfy%20the%20subjective-culpability%20requirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263164-james-vandevender-v-walter-sass-decision%23document%2Fp9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edismissed%20the%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20Vandevender%20could%20take%20discovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Vandevender%20appealed%2C%20the%208th%20Circuit%20agreed%20with%20Frank%2C%20deciding%20that%20Vandevender%20was%20the%20victim%20of%20a%20surprise%20attack%20and%20that%20corrections%20officers%20therefore%20could%20not%20have%20violated%20his%20rights%20by%20failing%20to%20protect%20him.%20The%20court%20determined%20that%20the%20prior%20assault%20with%20a%20wooden%20pitchfork%20handle%20hadn't%20signaled%20a%20%26quot%3Bpervasive%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20BI%20spoke%20with%20Mark%20Bradford%2C%20Vandevender's%20attorney%2C%20two%20years%20after%20he%20lost%20the%20case%2C%20he%20seemed%20defeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20sure%20what%20more%20you%20could%20possibly%20do%20to%20show%20deliberate%20indifference%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20is%20a%20troubling%20standard%20that%20the%208th%20Circuit%20has%20employed%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppended%20to%20the%20appeals%20court's%20judgment%20is%20a%20separate%20opinion%2C%20authored%20by%20Judge%20Jane%20Kelly%2C%20who%20wrote%20that%20she%20concurred%20only%20because%20she%20was%20bound%20by%208th%20Circuit%20precedent.%20%26quot%3BOur%20caselaw%20may%20set%20the%20bar%20too%20high%20for%20the%20typical%20inmate%20to%20sufficiently%20plead%20prison%20officials%20were%20deliberately%20indifferent%20to%20a%20substantial%20risk%20of%20serious%20harm%20in%20a%20case%20like%20this%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b365c05f-d9a3-4df4-9f52-c749e5d57968%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'The%20easiest%20lie%20to%20tell'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Eighth%20Amendment%20cases%20BI%20reviewed%20include%20claims%20of%20untreated%20cancers%20and%20heart%20disease%2C%20retaliatory%20beatings%2C%20sexual%20assaults%2C%20limb%20amputations%2C%20and%20prisoners%20wasting%20away%20in%20squalid%20cells%20littered%20with%20feces%20and%20dead%20flies.%20There%20was%20a%20New%20York%20teenager%20who%20said%20he%20was%20put%20in%20a%20vermin-infested%20cell%20in%20late%202021%20where%20he%20was%20attacked%20by%20a%20bat%20and%20bitten%20by%20a%20poisonous%20spider%2C%20an%20Arizona%20prisoner%20who%20said%20in%202020%20he%20was%20given%20only%20Tylenol%20to%20treat%20a%20broken%20jaw%2C%20and%20a%20Michigan%20man%20who%20filed%20a%20complaint%20in%202019%20saying%20his%20eyesight%20deteriorated%20because%20prison%20doctors%20refused%20to%20conduct%20cataract%20surgery.%20Again%20and%20again%2C%20courts%20dismissed%20these%20cases%2C%20finding%20that%20prisoners%20had%20failed%20to%20meet%20the%20deliberate-indifference%20standard.%20The%20standard%20introduced%20three%20decades%20ago%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20interpretation%20by%20federal%20courts%20in%20the%20years%20since%20%E2%80%94%20has%20created%20formidable%20obstacles%20to%20accountability%20in%20this%20country's%20prisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22David%20Fathi%20in%20a%20suit%20at%20the%20ACLU%20offices.%20A%20sign%20beghind%20him%20reads%20%26quot%3BVote%20to%20end%20mass%20incarceration.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675360228fbb2783ed306569%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDavid%20Fathi%2C%20who%20directs%20the%20ACLU's%20National%20Prison%20Project%2C%20described%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20deliberate-indifference%20standard%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20enormous%20barrier%20to%20justice%20for%20incarcerated%20people.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Arizona%20Department%20of%20Corrections%2C%20Rehabilitation%20%26amp%3B%20Reentry%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20broken-jaw%20claim%20but%20said%20that%20Gov.%20Katie%20Hobbs%20had%20appointed%20a%20new%20corrections%20director%2C%20Ryan%20Thornell%2C%20in%20January%202023%20%26quot%3Bto%20make%20needed%20changes%20to%20the%20correctional%20system%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he%20was%20ensuring%20%26quot%3Bhigh-quality%2C%20patient-centered%20care%20and%20wellness%20are%20becoming%20standard%20practice.%26quot%3B%20The%20New%20York%20and%20Michigan%20corrections%20departments%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20cases%20in%20BI's%20sample%2C%201%2C361%20were%20argued%20under%20the%20deliberate-indifference%20standard.%20Only%2010%20plaintiffs%20prevailed%20in%20court%3B%20another%20164%20cases%20settled%20without%20the%20prison%20admitting%20liability.%20All%2010%20of%20the%20successful%20plaintiffs%20were%20among%20the%20minority%20in%20the%20sample%20who%20were%20represented%20by%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftbimedia.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbistudios%2F_00%2Fdev_edit%2Fgraphics%2F2024%2F12%2F2024-12-14-8A-GRAPHIC03%2Findex.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-chart%3D%5C%22ai2html-8AGV03%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Fathi%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Prison%20Project%20at%20the%20ACLU%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20standard%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Ban%20enormous%20barrier%20to%20justice%20for%20incarcerated%20people.%26quot%3B%20If%20prisoners%20encounter%20conditions%20that%20are%20%26quot%3Binhumane%2C%20unhealthy%2C%20dangerous%2C%20or%20even%20lethal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20argued%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20should%20be%20enough%20to%20violate%20the%20Eighth%20Amendment%20%E2%80%94%20you%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20go%20looking%20for%20someone%20who%20was%20thinking%20bad%20thoughts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Shapiro%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Chicago%20Lawyers'%20Committee%20for%20Civil%20Rights%2C%20has%20litigated%20dozens%20of%20Eighth%20Amendment%20cases%20on%20behalf%20of%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EI%20didn't%20know%3C%2Fem%3E%20this%20person%20was%20going%20to%20get%20attacked%20by%20another%20incarcerated%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20defenses%20under%20the%20deliberate-indifference%20standard.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EI%20didn't%20know%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20this%20person%20was%20having%20chest%20pains%20because%20they%20were%20experiencing%20a%20heart%20attack.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20prison%20officials%20assert%20that%20they%20didn't%20know%20about%20the%20risk%2C%20he%20said%2C%20a%20federal%20court%20will%20rarely%20find%20an%20Eighth%20Amendment%20violation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20the%20easiest%20lie%20to%20tell%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EI%20didn't%20know%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f96c9f2-628d-47e6-913c-a0158a6e16aa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'A%20dark%20and%20evil%20world'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20generations%2C%20the%20federal%20courts%20took%20a%20mostly%20hands-off%20approach%20to%20conditions%20in%20America's%20prisons.%20That%20changed%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Movement%2C%20as%20judges%20began%20to%20issue%20Eighth%20Amendment%20rulings%20that%20secured%20key%20rights%20for%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201970%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20put%20every%20Arkansas%20prison%20under%20court%20order%2C%20calling%20the%20state%20system%20%26quot%3Ba%20dark%20and%20evil%20world%20completely%20alien%20to%20the%20free%20world.%26quot%3B%20Six%20years%20later%2C%20another%20federal%20judge%20found%20prisons%20in%20Alabama%20%26quot%3Bwholly%20unfit%20for%20human%20habitation%26quot%3B%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20this%20time%2C%20a%20Texas%20prisoner%20named%20J.W.%20Gamble%20sued%20his%20facility%20over%20inadequate%20medical%20care%2C%20arguing%20that%20officers%20had%20failed%20to%20treat%20his%20intense%20pain%20after%20a%20600-pound%20cotton%20bale%20fell%20on%20him%20during%20a%20work%20assignment.%20While%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20found%20that%20Gamble's%20constitutional%20rights%20hadn't%20been%20violated%2C%20the%201976%20decision%2C%20written%20by%20Thurgood%20Marshall%2C%20established%20that%20prisoners%20have%20a%20right%20to%20medical%20care%20under%20the%20Eighth%20Amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDeliberate%20indifference%20to%20serious%20medical%20needs%20of%20prisoners%20constitutes%20the%20'unnecessary%20and%20wanton%20infliction%20of%20pain%2C'%26quot%3B%20Marshall%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAn%20inmate%20must%20rely%20on%20prison%20authorities%20to%20treat%20his%20medical%20needs%3B%20if%20the%20authorities%20fail%20to%20do%20so%2C%20those%20needs%20will%20not%20be%20met.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20consequential%20decision.%20It%20was%20also%2C%20fatefully%2C%20the%20court's%20introduction%20of%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bdeliberate%20indifference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20it%20sat%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Boston%2C%20the%20former%20director%20of%20the%20Prisoners'%20Rights%20Project%20of%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Legal%20Aid%20Society%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20vulnerable%20to%20a%20more%20conservative%20court%20coming%20along%20and%20trying%20to%20define%20it%20downward%20in%20ways%20disadvantageous%20to%20prisoners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20shift%20occurred%20quickly.%20As%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20ramped%20up%20the%20war%20on%20drugs%2C%20legislators%20from%20both%20parties%2C%20committed%20to%20a%20tough-on-crime%20agenda%2C%20began%20to%20pass%20a%20raft%20of%20criminal-justice%20measures.%20The%20impact%20of%20these%20policies%20is%20now%20well%20known.%20In%20less%20than%2030%20years%20the%20country's%20penal%20population%20grew%20sixfold%20to%20a%20peak%20of%20more%20than%202%20million%2C%20leaving%20the%20US%20incarcerating%20more%20people%20than%20any%20other%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20critical%20Farmer%20v.%20Brennan%20case%20came%20when%20Dee%20Farmer%2C%20a%20transgender%20woman%2C%20filed%20a%20claim%20saying%20federal%20prison%20officials%20had%20failed%20to%20protect%20her%20from%20sexual%20assault.%20In%20an%20interview%2C%20she%20described%20how%2C%20after%20being%20raped%20by%20another%20prisoner%20at%20knifepoint%2C%20she%20was%20sent%20to%20segregation%20for%20over%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Farmer%20won%20her%20case%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20it%20was%20hailed%20as%20a%20major%20victory%20for%20transgender%20rights.%20The%20decision%20also%20cemented%20the%20current%20deliberate-indifference%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dee%20Farmer%20sits%20in%20a%20room%20with%20writing%20on%20a%20whiteboard%20behind%20her.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675360ad8fb3f94e507402e5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDee%20Farmer%20was%20the%20first%20out%20transgender%20plaintiff%20to%20have%20a%20case%20heard%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20She%20prevailed%20in%201994%2C%20but%20the%20standard%20established%20in%20the%20Farmer%20decision%20has%20stymied%20prisoners'%20Eighth%20Amendment%20claims.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFarmer's%20lead%20attorney%2C%20the%20ACLU's%20foremost%20prison%20expert%2C%20Elizabeth%20Alexander%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20standard%20should%20hinge%20on%20what%20officials%20had%20the%20professional%20responsibility%20to%20know.%20The%20solicitor%20general%2C%20Drew%20Days%20III%2C%20disagreed%2C%20contending%20that%20officials%20should%20be%20held%20liable%20only%20for%20risks%20they%20were%20aware%20of.%20%26quot%3BPetitioner's%20'should%20have%20known'%20approach%20ignores%20the%20'deliberateness'%20requirement%20of%20the%20'deliberate%20indifference'%20standard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20brief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20agreed%20with%20Days%2C%20finding%20that%20officials%20were%20liable%20only%20if%20they%20personally%20knew%20of%20and%20disregarded%20the%20risk%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20harm%20to%20the%20prisoner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclearinghouse.net%2Fdoc%2F136524%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissued%20warnings%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%20Michelle%20Alexander%2C%20the%20noted%20civil-rights%20lawyer%20and%20author%2C%20who%20was%20then%20a%20clerk%20for%20Justice%20Harry%20Blackmun%2C%20suggested%20that%20the%20majority%20opinion%20%26quot%3Bwould%20allow%20a%20prison%20official%20to%20argue%20to%20the%20jury%20that%20although%20a%20particular%20risk%20of%20harm%20was%20plainly%20obvious%2C%20and%20a%20reasonable%20prison%20official%20would%20have%20been%20aware%20of%20it%2C%20he%20wasn't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20own%20concurring%20opinion%2C%20Blackmun%20described%20the%20new%20standard%20as%20fundamentally%20misguided.%20%26quot%3BA%20punishment%20is%20simply%20no%20less%20cruel%20or%20unusual%20because%20its%20harm%20is%20unintended%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%2C%20in%20a%20recent%20email%2C%20described%20the%20decision%20as%20one%20of%20many%20during%20that%20period%20that%20created%20what%20she%20called%20%26quot%3Bunconscionable%20obstacles%20to%20meaningful%20relief%20for%20people%20ensnared%20by%20our%20criminal%20injustice%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FsVUMO%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22GV11%3A%20Cases%20turn%20on%20the%20question%20of%20mindset%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22681%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EVandevender%20is%20one%20of%20hundreds%20of%20prisoners%20in%20BI's%20sample%20for%20whom%20those%20obstacles%20were%20insurmountable.%20Prisons%20are%20inherently%20dangerous%20places%2C%20the%208th%20Circuit%20concluded%20in%20his%20case%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Binmates%20bent%20on%20assaulting%20other%20inmates%20will%20use%20even%20the%20most%20harmless%20objects%20as%20weapons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20James%20Loken%2C%20who%20authored%20the%20majority%20opinion%2C%20wrote%20that%2C%20for%20Vandevender%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20outcome%20was%20tragic%2C%20and%20an%20assault%20with%20this%20weapon%20was%2C%20in%20hindsight%2C%20no%20doubt%20avoidable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20he%20concluded%20by%20quoting%20the%20Farmer%20decision%2C%20writing%2C%20%26quot%3Ban%20official's%20failure%20to%20alleviate%20a%20significant%20risk%20that%20he%20should%20have%20perceived%20but%20did%20not%2C%20while%20no%20cause%20for%20commendation%2C%20cannot%20under%20our%20cases%20be%20condemned%20as%20the%20infliction%20of%20Eighth%20Amendment%20punishment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228abf30b9-0f05-45f1-8fdb-8bd659bf0959%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20fianc%C3%A9e's%20warning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20after%20Latimer's%20assault%20on%20Vandevender%2C%20Rush%20City%20experienced%20another%20violent%20attack.%20This%20time%2C%20officials%20were%20repeatedly%20warned%20of%20the%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrina%20Murray%20was%20at%20home%20in%20bed%20one%20night%20when%20she%20got%20the%20call.%20She%20was%20confused%3B%20her%20daughter%20never%20phoned%20that%20late.%20She%20listened%20with%20a%20rising%20panic%20as%20she%20learned%20that%20her%20only%20son%2C%20David%20Hodges%2C%20had%20been%20assaulted%20at%20Rush%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trina%20Murray%20sits%20in%20her%20apartment%20holding%20a%20photo%20of%20her%20son%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67536b9e8fbb2783ed306880%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETrina%20Murray%20said%20she%20witnessed%20violence%20firsthand%20as%20a%20Minnesota%20corrections%20officer.%20Years%20later%2C%20her%20son%2C%20David%20Hodges%2C%20was%20assaulted%20while%20serving%20time%20at%20Rush%20City.%3Cp%3EPatience%20Zalanga%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHodges%20is%20a%20large%20man%2C%20tall%20and%20broad-shouldered%2C%20with%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20inked%20onto%20his%20right%20forearm.%20But%20Murray%20still%20worried%20about%20his%20exposure%20to%20violence%20when%2C%20in%202011%2C%20he%20was%20sent%20to%20prison%20for%20sexual%20assault.%20She%20knew%20what%20Minnesota's%20prisons%20could%20be%20like%2C%20having%20worked%20in%20two%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20tells%20one%20story%20from%20when%20she%20was%20an%20officer%20at%20Minnesota%20Correctional%20Facility%E2%80%93Lino%20Lakes%2C%20a%20medium-security%20prison%20outside%20Minneapolis%2C%20in%20the%201990s.%20There%2C%20in%20her%20telling%2C%20she%20witnessed%20a%20group%20of%20officers%20placing%20bets%20on%20how%20many%20prisoners%20they%20could%20send%20to%20solitary%20confinement.%20When%20she%20reported%20the%20behavior%2C%20she%20became%20the%20target%20of%20a%20campaign%20of%20retaliation.%20The%20officers%2C%20all%20men%2C%20followed%20her%20to%20her%20car.%20They%20called%20her%20the%20N-word%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20told%20her%20to%20go%20back%20to%20Africa.%20Later%20someone%20threw%20a%20rock%20through%20the%20window%20of%20her%20home.%20Eventually%2C%20she%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20call%20that%20evening%20in%20September%202018%2C%20she%20scrambled%20to%20learn%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20her%20son.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263190-david-hodges-incident-report%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincident%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263179-david-hodges-investigation-report%23document%2Fp9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigative%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263186-david-hodges-disciplinary-report%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Hodges%20claimed%20that%20another%20prisoner%2C%20Courtney%20Osgood%2C%20had%20entered%20his%20cell%20with%20a%20shank%2C%20angry%20that%20Hodges%20had%20refused%20to%20pay%20off%20a%20debt%20owed%20by%20Hodges'%20cellmate.%20Osgood%20grabbed%20Hodges'%20locs%2C%20ripping%20some%20out%2C%20and%20attempted%20to%20stab%20him.%20Hodges%2C%20who%20had%20been%20making%20coffee%20on%20a%20small%20hotplate%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263192-david-hodges-incident-report-ii%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethrew%20the%20boiling%20water%20at%20Osgood%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20raced%20out%20of%20the%20cell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrison%20officials%20weren't%20aware%20of%20the%20altercation%2C%20according%20to%20an%20incident%20report%2C%20until%20Hodges'%20then-fianc%C3%A9e%20called%20the%20prison%2C%20concerned%20about%20his%20safety.%20Once%20alerted%2C%20Hodges'%20subsequent%20civil%20complaint%20said%2C%20they%20sentenced%20Osgood%20to%2020%20days%20in%20segregation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20gave%20twice%20that%20to%20Hodges.%20Gene%20Olson%2C%20a%20prison%20lieutenant%20who%20investigated%20the%20incident%2C%20said%20in%20a%20deposition%20that%20he%20couldn't%20prove%20Hodges'%20account%20of%20the%20attempted%20stabbing%20because%20officials%20couldn't%20track%20down%20the%20shank.%20Osgood%20also%20denied%20Hodges'%20account%20in%20a%20message%20to%20BI%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bfabricated%20narrative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263200-david-hodges-disciplinary-report%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esegregation%20for%20about%20six%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20locked%20in%20a%20tiny%20cell%2C%20the%20lights%20on%2018%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20Hodges%20said%2C%20he%20obsessed%20about%20one%20thing%3A%20what%20was%20waiting%20for%20him%20when%20he%20got%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20prison%20politics%20101%2C%20if%20I%20assault%20you%20and%20I%20hurt%20you%20real%20bad%2C%20you're%20looking%20to%20get%20your%20lick%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNeedless%20to%20say%2C%20I'm%20a%20big%20guy%2C%20and%20I%20know%20this%20time%20he%20was%20coming%20with%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223453%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22David%20Hodges%20standing%20on%20a%20sidewalk.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67536be48fbb2783ed30688c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHodges%20filed%20suit%20in%202020%20claiming%20Rush%20City%20officials%20had%20failed%20to%20protect%20him%20from%20a%20fellow%20prisoner's%20attack.%20A%20federal%20court%20said%20he%20hadn't%20proven%20the%20officials%20were%20deliberately%20indifferent.%3Cp%3EPatience%20Zalanga%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHodges%20begged%20officers%20to%20move%20him%20to%20a%20different%20unit%2C%20verbally%20and%20in%20writing.%20Murray%2C%20his%20mother%2C%20along%20with%20his%20fianc%C3%A9e%2C%20his%20sister%2C%20and%20his%20grandmother%2C%20called%20and%20wrote%20over%20a%20period%20of%20six%20weeks%20to%20the%20prison%20and%20to%20state%20corrections%20headquarters%2C%20imploring%20officials%20to%20take%20action%20because%20they%20feared%20for%20his%20life.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20exactly%20must%20he%20do%20to%20get%20a%20transfer%20to%20another%20facility%20for%20his%20safety%3F%26quot%3B%20his%20fianc%C3%A9e%20asked%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263211-david-hodges-v-minnesota-doc-emails%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20late-October%20email%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20warden%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Jeffrey%20Titus.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20must%20something%20really%20bad%20happen%20before%20he%20is%20taken%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20prison%20in%20Minnesota%20has%20an%20incompatibility-review%20committee%20composed%20of%20prison%20staff%20that%20meets%20to%20decide%20whether%20particular%20prisoners%20pose%20a%20risk%20to%20each%20other%20and%20need%20to%20be%20separated.%20Their%20deliberations%2C%20a%20former%20corrections%20staffer%20at%20Rush%20City%20told%20BI%2C%20are%20usually%20documented%20in%20great%20detail.%20Rush%20City's%20panel%2C%20which%20included%20Olson%2C%20had%20met%20in%20late%20September%202018%20and%20decided%20that%20Hodges%20and%20Osgood%20didn't%20need%20to%20be%20separated.%20Ashlee%20Berts%2C%20a%20corrections%20program%20director%20who%20oversaw%20the%20committee%2C%2