him.%20Hodges%20was%20attacked%20again%20not%20long%20after.%3Cp%3EMinnesota%20Department%20of%20Corrections%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20November%2C%20just%20hours%20after%20Hodges%20was%20released%20from%20segregation%2C%20Osgood%20and%20a%20fellow%20prisoner%20assaulted%20him%20in%20the%20living%20unit%2C%20throwing%20a%20mixture%20of%20hot%20water%20and%20capsaicin%2C%20a%20chili-pepper%20extract%2C%20in%20his%20face.%20Surveillance%20video%20shows%20Hodges%20trying%20to%20escape%20as%20the%20two%20men%20come%20toward%20him.%20They%20land%20a%20series%20of%20punches%20as%20Hodges%20waves%20his%20arms%20in%20a%20futile%20attempt%20to%20make%20contact%20with%20his%20assailants.%20His%20eyes%20were%20blinded%20and%20burning%2C%20he%20told%20BI%2C%20saying%20it%20felt%20like%20an%20eternity%20before%20officers%20arrived.%20Medical%20records%20show%20he%20suffered%20a%20nasal%20fracture%2C%20second-degree%20burns%2C%20and%20an%20eye%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20days%20after%20the%20assault%2C%20the%20committee%20made%20a%20new%20determination%3A%20Hodges%20and%20Osgood%20were%20incompatible%2C%20and%20Hodges'%20transfer%20request%20was%20granted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20five%20years%20later%2C%20Hodges%20discussed%20the%20incident%20while%20sitting%20in%20an%20empty%20visitors'%20room%20at%20Minnesota%20Correctional%20Facility%E2%80%93Moose%20Lake%2C%20a%20state%20hospital%20turned%20prison%20an%20hour%20north%20of%20Rush%20City.%20The%20window%20blinds%20concealed%20a%20barbed-wire%20fence%20just%20outside.%20He%20wears%20wire-framed%20glasses%20now%2C%20to%20help%20with%20the%20blurred%20vision%20he's%20lived%20with%20since%20the%20attack.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20sleepless%20nights%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20I%20think%20about%20the%20situation%2C%20I'll%20have%20flashbacks.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20July%202019%20incident%20report%2C%20an%20officer%20described%20finding%20him%20crying%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20an%20anxiety%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Vandevender%20before%20him%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263291-david-hodges-v-minnesota-doc-complaint%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHodges%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleging%20that%20prison%20officials%20at%20Rush%20City%20failed%20to%20keep%20him%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Exterior%20of%20Minnesota%20Correctional%20Facility-Moose%20Lake%2C%20with%20red%20brick%20walls%20topped%20by%20razor%20wire%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675366e54adc4cc134352dca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMinnesota%20Correctional%20Facility%E2%80%93Moose%20Lake%2C%20a%20prison%20where%20Hodges%20served%20time%20after%20Rush%20City.%3Cp%3EPatience%20Zalanga%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Vandevender%2C%20the%20court's%20ruling%20hinged%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20he'd%20experienced%20a%20surprise%20attack.%20But%20the%20attack%20on%20Hodges%20came%20after%20a%20campaign%20of%20urgent%20warnings%20that%20he%20feared%20for%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defendants%20argued%20that%20launching%20the%20incompatibility%20review%20was%20itself%20proof%20they%20hadn't%20been%20deliberately%20indifferent%20to%20Hodges'%20welfare.%20A%20federal%20judge%2C%20Wilhelmina%20Wright%2C%20accepted%20the%20officers'%20claim%20that%20they%20had%20determined%20in%20good%20faith%20that%20Osgood%20no%20longer%20posed%20a%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20this%20conclusion%20proved%20to%20be%20incorrect%20does%20not%20demonstrate%20that%20Defendants%20recklessly%20or%20intentionally%20ignored%20an%20obvious%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20wrote%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25263292-david-hodges-v-minnesota-doc-decision%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeciding%20in%20the%20officers'%20favor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%208th%20Circuit%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20appeals%20court%20that%20decided%20Vandevender's%20case%20%E2%80%94%20agreed%20with%20Wright%20on%20appeal%2C%20finding%20that%20the%20officials%20had%20simply%20%26quot%3Bpredicted%20incorrectly.%26quot%3B%20Hodges'%20claim%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de217a20-5337-4148-b739-9103243e7980%5C%22%3EA%20modern-day%20'Lord%20of%20the%20Flies'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sample%20BI%20analyzed%20is%20full%20of%20cases%20in%20which%20officers%20failed%20to%20act%20on%20warnings%20that%20prisoners%20were%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarc%20Bakambia%2C%20another%20Rush%20City%20prisoner%2C%20said%20that%20after%20a%20group%20of%20prisoners%20beat%20him%20up%20and%20threw%20him%20over%20a%20railing%2C%20he%20was%20placed%20in%20their%20same%20unit%20and%20assaulted%20again%2C%20leaving%20him%20with%20bone%20fractures%20and%20a%20traumatic%20brain%20injury.%20Craig%20Shipp%20claimed%20he%20had%20sought%20orthotic%20shoes%20for%20his%20diabetes%20and%20degenerative%20joint%20disorder%20but%20Arkansas%20prison%20and%20medical%20staff%20denied%20his%20repeated%20requests%3B%20he%20said%20he%20eventually%20developed%20an%20infection%20severe%20enough%20to%20result%20in%20the%20amputation%20of%20his%20right%20foot.%20Mitchell%20Marbury%20claimed%20he%20requested%20a%20transfer%20after%20a%20friend%20warned%20him%20that%20a%20fellow%20prisoner%20was%20out%20to%20get%20him%3B%20he%20said%20an%20Alabama%20corrections%20officer%20laughed%20and%20told%20him%20to%20get%20a%20shank.%20Less%20than%20a%20week%20later%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he%20was%20stabbed%20in%20the%20facility's%20day%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Arkansas%20and%20Alabama%20corrections%20departments%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%3B%20the%20Minnesota%20corrections%20department%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20Bakambia%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMarbury's%20argument%20is%20essentially%20that%20every%20prisoner%20who%20tells%20prison%20officials%20about%20an%20unspecified%20threat%20from%20an%20unspecified%20inmate%20without%20more%20is%20entitled%20to%20protective%20custody%20or%20a%20transfer%2C%26quot%3B%2011th%20Circuit%20judges%20wrote%20in%20the%20majority%20opinion.%20%26quot%3BOur%20caselaw%20establishes%20a%20higher%20standard%20for%20deliberate%20indifference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Eighth%20Amendment%20does%20not%20allow%20prisons%20to%20be%20modern-day%20settings%20for%20%3Cem%3ELord%20of%20the%20Flies%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Judge%20Robin%20Rosenbaum%20wrote%20in%20a%20scathing%20dissent.%20By%20not%20holding%20officials%20responsible%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Majority%20Opinion%20condones%20this%20behavior%20and%20ensures%20it%20will%20occur%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reviewing%20Hodges'%20appeal%2C%20Kelly%2C%20the%208th%20Circuit%20judge%2C%20wrote%20her%20own%20opinion%2C%20as%20she%20had%20in%20the%20Vandevender%20case.%20She%20disagreed%20with%20how%20her%20colleagues%20assessed%20the%20question%20of%20mindset%2C%20writing%20that%20a%20committee%20finding%20alone%20should%20not%20release%20prison%20officials%20from%20liability.%20She%20also%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20absence%20of%20documentation%20regarding%20prison%20decisions%20or%20prison%20officials'%20inability%20to%20remember%20events%20central%20to%20their%20decision-making%20process%20may%20be%20relevant%2C%26quot%3B%20raising%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20those%20gaps%20could%20have%20been%20deliberate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20corrections%20officers%20are%20made%20aware%20of%20the%20mindset%20standard.%20BI%20requested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fprojects%2F220061-corrections-training-materials%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficer%20training%20materials%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20every%20state%20pr