22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25448282-mississippi-department-of-corrections-legal-liabilities-training%2F%3Fmode%3Ddocument%26q%3Dcompromise%2Btheir%2Bintegrity%23document%2Fp19%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMississippi%20slide%20deck%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20corrections%20officials%20were%20told%20prisoners%20try%20to%20compromise%20their%20integrity%20%26quot%3Bas%20entertainment%20and%20for%20their%20amusement%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bto%20facilitate%20an%20escape%2C%20assault%2C%20rape%20or%20murder.%26quot%3B%20A%20slide%20in%20a%202018%20Utah%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25448366-utah-department-of-corrections-2018-inmate-civil-rights-litigation-training%2F%3Fmode%3Ddocument%23document%2Fp2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraining%20PowerPoint%3C%2Fa%3E%20displayed%20the%20header%20%26quot%3Binmates%20do%20crazy%20things%E2%80%A6%20then%20sue%20YOU%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20good%20to%20train%20them%20on%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Fathi%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20should%20also%20make%20clear%20that%20we%20expect%20more%20than%20the%20absolute%20minimum%20that's%20required%20to%20avoid%20violating%20the%20Constitution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22928cb181-f8c1-42ed-a855-c6b4898a7912%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMemory%20issues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20muggy%20June%20morning%20in%202023%2C%20as%20the%20sun%20was%20just%20beginning%20to%20peak%20out%20in%20Euless%2C%20Texas%2C%20James%20Vandevender%20was%20already%20up%20in%20his%20father's%20modest%20one-story%20house%20in%20the%20Dallas%20suburb%2C%20pouring%20himself%20a%20cup%20of%20coffee.%20He%20had%20moved%20there%20from%20Minnesota%2C%20after%20his%20last%20prison%20stint%2C%20looking%20for%20a%20fresh%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20dressed%20in%20khakis%20for%20his%20job%20installing%20high-end%20appliances.%20A%20tattoo%20of%20his%20son's%20name%20showed%20below%20his%20shirt%20sleeve%2C%20and%20a%20scar%20cut%20across%20his%20cropped%20brown%20hair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20moved%20through%20the%20same%20routine%20as%20every%20morning%3A%20packing%20his%20lunchbox%2C%20scarfing%20down%20breakfast%2C%20and%20swallowing%20an%20array%20of%20anti-seizure%20pills%20and%20antidepressants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22James%20Vandevender%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6753619e4adc4cc134352c92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVandevender%20has%20lived%20with%20persistent%20memory%20problems%20since%20the%20attack.%3Cp%3EShelby%20Tauber%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20that%20day%2C%20he%20forgot%20to%20put%20the%20ice%20pack%20in%20his%20lunchbox%20and%20had%20to%20redo%20it.%20When%20he%20headed%20outside%20to%20toss%20out%20the%20trash%2C%20he%20couldn't%20remember%20where%20he%20stowed%20the%20garbage%20bins.%20By%20the%20time%20he%20and%20his%20coworkers%20gassed%20up%20and%20headed%20off%20to%20the%20first%20house%2C%20Vandevender%20had%20misplaced%20his%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20wrapped%20up%20their%20first%20job%20and%20headed%20back%20to%20their%20truck%2C%20Vandevender%20realized%20he'd%20left%20his%20tool%20bag%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20next%20house%2C%20the%20men%20were%20tasked%20with%20installing%20a%20mounted%20range%20hood%20they'd%20never%20encountered%20before.%20It%20was%20a%20tricky%20job%2C%20Vandevender%20said.%20By%20late%20afternoon%2C%20visibly%20frustrated%2C%20he%20called%20the%20installation%20a%20%26quot%3Bfucking%20joke.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20coworker%20Mike%2C%20in%20a%20black%20baseball%20cap%20to%20protect%20from%20the%20sweltering%20sun%2C%20took%20a%20breather%20in%20the%20driveway%2C%20away%20from%20the%20tension%20inside.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20been%20having%20memory%20issues%20all%20day%20long.%20It's%20an%20everyday%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20Vandevender.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20when%20he%20gets%20frustrated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAshley%20Christen%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20Vandevender's%2020-year-old%20son%2C%20said%20that%20when%20the%20two%20of%20them%20were%20growing%20up%20in%20rural%20Minnesota%2C%20Vandevender%20was%20smart%20and%20quick-witted%2C%20known%20for%20delivering%20the%20best%20one-liners.%20As%20a%20kid%2C%20he%20loved%20to%20hunt%20and%20spend%20time%20on%20his%20grandfather's%20dairy%20farm%3B%20his%20mother%2C%20Peggy%2C%20said%20he%20was%20fun%20and%20lovable%2C%20always%20offering%20to%20help%20out%20around%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20the%20assault%2C%20they%20both%20said%2C%20he's%20struggled%20to%20communicate.%20He's%20forgetful%2C%20irritable%2C%20and%20prone%20to%20snap.%20Peggy%20said%20he%20relied%20on%20scribbled%20notes%20to%20get%20through%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20shouldn't%20have%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20because%20of%20their%20lack%20of%20watching%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20due%20to%20their%20negligence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20recent%20fall%20afternoon%2C%2012%20years%20after%20Latimer%20bludgeoned%20him%20with%20the%20wooden%20post%2C%20Vandevender%20sat%20down%20with%20a%20friend%20to%20watch%20surveillance%20footage%20of%20the%20attack%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20He%20doesn't%20remember%20anything%20from%20that%20day%3B%20his%20first%20recollection%20is%20waking%20up%20weeks%20later%2C%20confused%20and%20shackled%2C%20in%20a%20hospital%20bed%20flanked%20by%20corrections%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20you're%20mentally%20prepared%20to%20see%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20friend%20told%20him%2C%20before%20pressing%20play.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Vandevender%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20video%20finished%2C%20there%20was%20a%20long%20silence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20of%20destroyed%20American%20flag%20andJ%20ames%20Vandevender%20showing%20his%20back%20tattoo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675364648fbb2783ed3066aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20home%20in%20Euless%2C%20Texas%2C%20where%20Vandevender%20moved%20after%20his%20release%20from%20prison%3B%20scars%20from%20the%20violent%20prison%20assault%20remain%20visible%20on%20his%20scalp.%3Cp%3EShelby%20Tauber%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20he%20started%20talking.%20He%20said%20the%20footage%20took%20him%20back%20to%20his%20time%20in%20prison%20%E2%80%94%20the%20smell%2C%20the%20barbed%20wire%2C%20the%20disrespect.%20He%20said%20that%20he%20noticed%20Latimer%20picked%20up%20the%20post%20from%20an%20unauthorized%20part%20of%20the%20industry%20area%2C%20where%20prisoners%20weren't%20allowed%2C%20and%20that%20any%20unused%20lumber%20should%20have%20been%20disposed%20of.%20He%20said%20he%20felt%20the%20weight%20of%20what%20it%20must%20have%20been%20like%20for%20his%20mother%2C%20when%20she%20got%20the%20call%20every%20parent%20of%20an%20incarcerated%20child%20dreads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20life%20he%20could%20have%20had%2C%20the%20one%20where%20he%20got%20out%20of%20prison%20at%20age%2025%20without%20the%20burdens%20of%20a%20traumatic%20brain%20injury%2C%20he%20struggled%20to%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeliberate-indifference-standard-prisoner-abuse-rights-court-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734772141000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67535dc5